About me

I am from Ukraine and obtained my bachelor's degree in Software Development in Poland. I enjoy hiking in the mountains with a fun group, knitting, and spending time with my dog.

Quick Learner and Adaptive

I possess a remarkable ability to quickly grasp new concepts and adapt to dynamic work environments. With strong time management skills, I efficiently organize my tasks to meet deadlines, ensuring optimal productivity.

Additionally, my capacity to work independently allows me to thrive in various situations, taking initiative and delivering results autonomously.

Strategic Problem-Solver

With strong analytical and organizational skills, I excel at dissecting complex problems and devising effective solutions. I approach challenges methodically, breaking them down into manageable tasks and implementing systematic approaches for resolution. My critical and strategic thinking abilities enable me to tackle obstacles with confidence and precision.

Enthusiastic Creator and Coder

My passion for development stems from its unique blend of creative work and logical problem-solving, two aspects I deeply enjoy. Each coding challenge presents an opportunity to exercise both my imagination and analytical skills, fueling my commitment to delivering exceptional work and making meaningful contributions to every project.

Unconventional Thinker

As someone who thinks unconventionally, I thrive on approaching problems from unique angles. My ability to think outside the box allows me to devise innovative solutions that others might overlook. By embracing unconventional thinking, I aim to bring fresh perspectives and drive impactful outcomes in my work.
